2.00	Shiranui	Shiranui (Optical phenomenon)	Shiranui unknown fire, Shiranuhi in the historical kana orthography) is an optical phenomenon characterized by moving, changing fires which appear on the horizon of the Ariake Sea and the Yatsushiro Sea, Kumamoto Prefecture, Japan on the night of special days (August 1 of Chinese calendar). It had been long believed to be a mysterious, fiery y≈çkai, but today, scientific explanation has been made and it may appear on other days,too. It is a mixture of mirage.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/63/Tenryo_Shiranui.jpg/240px-Tenryo_Shiranui.jpg
